# stream-fork — AI Agent Rules

## Project identity

`stream-fork` is a toolkit of 1→N stream combinators: Writables that distribute every chunk to N downstream Writables under different dispatch shapes, with proper backpressure handling. Three primitives: `fork` (broadcast), `route` (per-chunk picker → one output), `filter` (per-chunk predicate per output → subset). The npm package name is `stream-fork`. Part of the `stream-chain` / `stream-json` family.

## Critical rules

- **CommonJS.** The project is `"type": "commonjs"`. Use `require()` in source, `import` in tests (`.mjs`).
- **No transpilation.** Code runs directly.
- **Zero runtime dependencies.** `dependencies: {}` is a hard rule.
- **Backpressure is the whole point.** Each primitive only signals "ready for the next chunk" once every **receiving** downstream has called back. Receiving set: every live output (`fork`), the single picked output (`route`), the predicate-matched subset (`filter`). Do not short-circuit the gate.
- **Built on a shared `makeStreamPusher`.** All primitives write through `src/stream-pusher.js`, which wraps `stream.write`/`stream.end` in a Promise-based interface and installs its own `'error'` listener.
- **Object mode default.** Every primitive forces `objectMode: true` unless caller overrides.
- **Dead-output handling.** Failed downstreams are marked dead by the pusher and filtered out of subsequent writes; the live set is exposed via `.outputs` and `.isEmpty()`.
- **Do not modify or delete test expectations** without understanding why they changed.
- **Do not add comments or remove comments** unless explicitly asked.
- **Keep `.js` and `.d.ts` files in sync** for every source file.

## Code style

- Prettier: 100 char width, single quotes, no bracket spacing, no trailing commas, arrow parens "avoid" (see `.prettierrc`).
- 2-space indentation.
- Semicolons are enforced by Prettier (default `semi: true`).
- Lambda-style functions except for generators (`function*`) and the rare `this`-dependent case.

## Architecture quick reference

- `fork(outputs, options?)` — broadcast Writable; every chunk goes to every live output.
- `route(outputs, options)` — single-target Writable; `options.pick(chunk, encoding)` picks the index. Non-index drops the chunk.
- `filter(outputs, options)` — subset Writable; `options.predicates[i](chunk, encoding)` decides whether output `i` receives the chunk.
- Picker helpers under `src/utils/`: `pickRoundRobin(count)`, `pickByHash(keyFn, count)`, `pickByKey(keyFn, table)`, `pickFirstMatch(predicates)`.
- Internal `makeStreamPusher(stream)` returns `{push, end, isDead, stream}` — every primitive uses it.

